profile_positions.description:
Direct report to corporate CFO, commissioned to put in place: # Global credit policy # Strengthen credit structure # Implement global Credit Risk management # Implement working capital improvements.

• Accountable of managing the global credit portfolio of well more than $150M together with a team of 6 FTE (centralized and de-centralized);
• Steering, coaching and monitoring team performance to ensure corporate KPIs are met;
• Global credit policy holder and ensuring compliancy;
• Control the cost to operate the credit and collection functions;
• Engage with customers in over 130 countries on a regular basis to assess business and finance performance and credit worthiness;
• Establish, approve and implement credit limits that reflect customers’ risk-profile;
• Work closely with the 5 regional business directors and their teams in facilitating business growth within the boundaries of the global credit policy, and agree collections and credit strategies;
• Accountable for administering customer’s master data, contracts and reflecting in ERP-system and downstream systems;
• Chair and drive the O2C process towards more efficiency and cost savings;
• Maintain relationship with third party service providers (banks, collection agencies, trade services providers and other parties;
• Frequently meet with senior management and remote teams to review Credit performance.
• Budget holder Credit Management

• Meeting customers on a regular basis to assess business performance and credit worthiness;
• Administering and enforcing company Credit Policies and procedures, assessing credit worthiness 
and recommending credit limits to senior management;
• Work closely with the shared service center to manage the regional collections portfolios;
• Thorough and in-depth analysis of financial statements for all customers and providing/sharing proactive
risk management/reporting to finance-  and sales management;
• Approve credit limits within credit authority based on appropriate and full credit package;
• Prepare thorough and full credit package including recommendation for senior management’s 
  approval for all credit lines in excess of $3M;
• Maintain appropriate documentation and transparency to support basis and rationale for customer 
credit decisions and limits;
• Monitor changes in economic, industry and customer conditions impacting potential customers' credit 
worthiness (risk tolerance);
• Making recommendations to reduce/control risk to EMEIA and WW senior management for all 
Credit lines;
• Prepare Cash Forecast and submit to Treasury team;
• Quarterly review and presentation of full portfolio to EMEIA- and WW senior management;
• Work closely with local senior management and remote teams to jointly review and closely monitor 
 portfolio performance.

• Meeting customers on a regular basis to assess business performance and credit worthiness;
	• Accountable of managing Credit & Collections portfolio of well over $500m;
	• Steering, coaching and monitoring team performance to ensure corporate KPIs are met;
	• Drive to achieve corporate ageing target of 2.0% or better of total outstanding receivable balance;
	• Maintain relationship with third party service providers (D&B, ACE, GE and others…);
	• Active involvement in the quarter-end financial closing of the credit process;
	• Prepare Cash Forecast and submit to Treasury team;
	• Frequently meet with senior management and remote teams to review Benelux portfolio.

• Leading and coaching credit and financial services team (7 FTE) managing portfolio of $350m;
• Developed and provided credit workshops to Credit team and Sales;
• Accountable for collecting all receivables, timely payments posting and all queries management;
• Accountable for administering customer’s master data, sales contracts and reflecting in SAP;
• Accountable for all credit & collections processes are performed as per corporate SOx policies;
• Prepare and report monthly cash forecast to EMEIA treasury manager;
• Monthly report bad debt accruals to Sr. EMEIA Credit manager;
• Weekly meet with sales management reviewing Benelux portfolio;
• Participation in several multidisciplinary European and global projects.

• Actively leading and coaching credit and financial services team (5 FTE);
• Accountable for collecting all receivables, timely payments posting and all queries management;
• Accountable for managing and maintaining customer- and contract master data;
• Quarterly review full credit portfolio with senior management;
• Maintain relationship with credit insurance companies;
• Subject Master Expert (SME) for all credit related maters;
• Participation in several multidisciplinary European and global projects.

• Put in place Benelux Credit & Collections team of 5 FTE (incl. 2 remote FTE) including tool, credit 
   policy and reporting to manage portfolio of $70m;
• Develop and provide credit workshops to Credit and Sales;
• Accountable for collecting all receivables, timely payments posting and all queries management;
• Participation in several multidisciplinary European and global projects.

• Accountable for timely and accurate financial accounting postings of all repair related transactions;
• Monthly financial reporting to group controller;
• Perform ad-hoc and random audits in compliance with company policy and report to controller;
• Participation in several multidisciplinary European and global projects.

• Leading operations team of 4 FTE from Zeist and Brussels;
• Ensuring overall customer satisfaction in accordance with service level agreement of 95% or better;
• Participation in several multidisciplinary European and global projects.
